<h2>Nginx</h2>
<p>Config path: <strong>{{nginxConfPath}}</strong></p>
<div class="row" style="align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-bottom:10px">
  <form method="post" action="/nginx/reload" onsubmit="return confirm('Reload nginx?')">
    <button class="btn ghost small">Reload Nginx</button>
  </form>
  <div class="muted">Command: <code class="kbd">{{nginxReloadCmd}}</code></div>
</div>

<h3>Create Site</h3>
<p class="hint">Create a new virtual host file and reload nginx. The panel will attempt to write into <code>/etc/nginx/sites-enabled</code> â€” set <code>NGINX_USE_SUDO=true</code> if the panel needs sudo to write there.</p>
<form class="nginx-form panel" method="post" action="/nginx/create-site" onsubmit="return confirm('Create site and reload nginx?')">
  <label>Domain
    <input name="domain" type="text" required placeholder="example.com">
  </label>

  <label>Root folder
    <input name="root" type="text" required placeholder="/data/web/example">
  </label>

  <div class="row">
    <div>
      <label>PHP-FPM host (optional)
        <input name="fpm_host" type="text" placeholder="127.0.0.1">
      </label>
    </div>
    <div>
      <label>PHP-FPM port (optional)
        <input name="fpm_port" type="text" placeholder="9000">
      </label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <label>Max upload body (optional)
    <input name="client_max_body_size" type="text" placeholder="128m">
  </label>

  <div class="hint small">Tip: set <code>fpm_port</code> to match your PHP-FPM listener (e.g. 9000 or 127.0.0.1:9999).</div>

  <button class="btn">Create site</button>
</form>

<div class="panel" style="margin-top:20px;">
  <h4>Host Helper Script</h4>
  <p class="hint small">If you've installed the host helper script, you can apply nginx site files with:</p>
  <code class="kbd">sudo /usr/local/bin/dfkpanel-apply-site /path/to/site.conf</code>
  <p class="hint small">See <code>HOST_SETUP.md</code> for installation instructions.</p>
</div>

<h3>Config File</h3>
{{#if error}}
  <pre class="error">{{content}}</pre>
{{else}}
  <pre class="code">{{content}}</pre>
{{/if}}
